                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17625620" author="blambov" created="Fri, 28 Oct 2022 11:19:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=benedict&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;benedict&quot;&gt;benedict&lt;/a&gt; , could you take a quick look at this? It&apos;s a one-line fix which looks good to me, but wondering if there&apos;s something we are missing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17625621" author="benedict" created="Fri, 28 Oct 2022 11:22:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix looks good, but is there a reason we&apos;re not using in-jvm dtests to introduce a regression test for this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also wanted to say good catch. I&apos;ve wanted for a while to expand the simulator to monitor availability, though it&apos;s a more difficult problem than testing that the isolation levels are maintained.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17626285" author="JIRAUSER297594" created="Sun, 30 Oct 2022 18:31:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=benedict&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;benedict&quot;&gt;benedict&lt;/a&gt;, thank you for your comment and suggestion to use in-jvm dtest. As requested, please note I submitted a relevant PR as per &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1961&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this link&lt;/a&gt;. If you have any further questions and/or concerns, please let me know.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cc&apos;ing: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blambov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blambov&quot;&gt;blambov&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mfleming&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mfleming&quot;&gt;mfleming&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17626716" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 31 Oct 2022 17:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;since Paxos v2 is 4.1, should this go into 4.1.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17628297" author="JIRAUSER297594" created="Thu, 3 Nov 2022 12:14:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt;, please note I have added a new PR for Cassandra 4.1.0 as per these links: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1966&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt; and&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1967&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;bug fix&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17629720" author="blambov" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2022 09:44:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This new PR is against 4.1, but it brings all the differences between trunk and 4.1. Checkout cassandra-4.1 into a new branch, cherry-pick the patch and then push the branch and create a pull request to 4.1 from it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, the in-jvm dtest, unlike the python dtest that lives in a separate repository, needs to be included in the main PR so that we can run CI tests. As the python dtest PR is no longer necessary, we can cancel and close that one too. That is, we should have one PR against 4.1 and one against trunk that include both the in-jvm dtest and bug fix (and only these changes).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17629746" author="JIRAUSER297594" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2022 10:36:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blambov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blambov&quot;&gt;blambov&lt;/a&gt;, sorry for the inconvenience and thank you for your comment, following which I closed the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra-dtest/pull/205&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Python dtest PR&lt;/a&gt; and raised the following two new PRs that include both the bug fix and the in-jvm dtest against:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1980&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;4.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/pull/1979&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;trunk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If you have any further questions/concerns, please let me know.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17629773" author="blambov" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2022 11:55:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tests started here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/blambov/cassandra/273/workflows/fb999a79-dd3d-4b70-843f-e88b3715ee6d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;trunk&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/blambov/cassandra/274/workflows/e26229be-0c9a-40f7-9066-7a23e341f49f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;4.1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17629802" author="blambov" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2022 12:57:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay, trunk tests are green and the 4.1 ones had 2 flakes on other tests in the repeated &lt;tt&gt;CASTest&lt;/tt&gt; which I believe are not caused by this. I&apos;m moving forward to committing the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17629805" author="blambov" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2022 13:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/acda6fad688e95e0a9a34de28e3b61a775e59736&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;acda6fad688e95e0a9a34de28e3b61a775e59736&lt;/a&gt; (4.1) and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/f236f40fc526dd75db648f4c6cc34d7f33fbd8f3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;f236f40fc526dd75db648f4c6cc34d7f33fbd8f3&lt;/a&gt; (trunk).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17629821" author="JIRAUSER297594" created="Mon, 7 Nov 2022 13:31:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for your update, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blambov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blambov&quot;&gt;blambov&lt;/a&gt;. That is great news! And also thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mfleming&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mfleming&quot;&gt;mfleming&lt;/a&gt; for your guidance and support throughout the process.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
